  %h2 What They Are Saying.....
  .double_content_border
  %p 
    Spot.Us is a platform that can be used by other news organizations to fundraise for their
    freelancers. Below are just some of the news organizations that have used Spot.Us to fund
    reporting projects. We also make our content available for them to republish.
    
  %h2 
    Featured partners we've worked with include....
  %p  
    %ul
      %li
        <a href="http://www.nytimes.com">The New York Times</a>
      %p
        We sent a reporter to the Pacific Garbage Patch who <a href="http://spot.us/stories/252-dissecting-the-great-pacific-garbage-patch">chronicled her voyage and published a
        final story in The New York Times</a>.
      %li
        Annenberg School of Communications at USC
      %p
        Our <a href="http://uscnews.usc.edu/digital_media/journalism_project_spotus_teams_with_usc_annenberg.html">partnering organization in Los Angeles</a>.
      %li
        Oakland Tribune
      %p
        With the Oakland Tribune we funded an investigation into the <a href="http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4176/is_20090617/ai_n31993719/">growing problem of potholes</a>. We
        also organized "the great pothole bike search" and produced <a href="http://www.insidebayarea.com/news/ci_11942436">a map that located major
        potholes in Oakland</a>.
      %li
        San Francisco Magazine
      %p
        Not every reporting project is text. With the San Francisco Magazine <a href="http://spot.us/stories/200-follow-the-trash-what-happens-to-your-recyclables">we funded an info
        graphic</a> on what happens to recycables in San Francisco.
      %li
        Earth Island Journal
      %p
        We have funded <a href="http://spot.us/stories/199-paul-ehrlich-the-vindication-of-a-public-scholar">two</a> feature projects for the Earth Island Journal.  
      %li
        East Bay Express and Making Contact (National Radio Project)
      %p
        We worked with the East Bay Express and National Radio Project to examine the <a href="http://spot.us/stories/241-breaking-the-wall-of-silence-civilian-oversight-of-police-in-oakland">citizen oversight of Oakland Police</a>. 
      %li
        KALW - Crosscurrents - NPR
      %p
        One of the NPR stations we are <a href="http://spot.us/pitches/265-crimes-courts-and-communities-in-the-bay-area">proud to fundraise for</a>.
      %li
        North Bay Bohemian, Palto Alto Weekly and the Sacramento News and Review
      %p
        All played a role in our collaboration to <a href="http://spot.us/pitches/337-investors-club-do-the-uc-regents-spin-public-funds-into-private-profit">investigate the regents of the University of California</a>.
      %li
        Oakland Local
      %p
        Our local sister organization which has used Spot.Us to <a href="http://spot.us/stories/341-more-than-ever-oakland-is-hungry">fund</a> <a href="http://spot.us/stories/303-parent-community-groups-fight-uphill-battle-to-reform-public-school-food">several</a> <a href="http://spot.us/stories/279-festival-of-grassroots-economics-asks-wheres-that-new-economy-offers-powerful-answers">stories</a>.
      %li
        The Public Press
      %p
        Our local brother organization which has used Spot.Us to fund several stories including the
        <a href="http://spot.us/stories/274-city-budget-watchdog-reporting-on-san-francisco-s-half-billion-dollar-hole">City Budget Watchdog</a> series and the <a href="http://spot.us/stories/344-the-bay-bridge-explained">Bay Bridge Explained Report</a>.
